In a #medium pot{}, bring @water{1 1/2%cups}, @milk{1/2%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} to a boil. Once boiling, slowly whisk in the @grits{1/2%cup}. Return to a boil, cover, and reduce to a low simmer for approximately ~{15%minutes}, stirring occasionally, until tender and creamy.

> TIP: If the grits become too dry, add a splash of water.

Prep the collard greens: Wash and dry all produce. Remove the ribs and stems from the @collard greens{4%oz} and roughly chop the leaves. Finely chop the @parsley{1/4%oz}. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Halve the @grape tomatoes{4%oz}.

Cook the collards: Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add the collards and cook, tossing for ~{4-5%minutes}, until lightly browned. Add the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Remove from the pan and set aside.

Add the tomatoes and a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} to the same #pan{} over medium-high heat. Cook, tossing for ~{3-4%minutes}, until beginning to burst. Set aside with the collard greens.

Heat another drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} in the same pan over medium-high heat. Season the @shrimp{10%oz} with @salt{pinch}, @pepper{pinch} and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%tsp} (to taste). Add to the pan and cook, tossing for ~{2-3%minutes}, until opaque. Add the collards, tomatoes, and parsley to the pan and cook, tossing, until warmed through.

Stir the @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} into the grits and season generously with salt and pepper. Serve the sautéed shrimp, collard greens, and tomatoes on top and enjoy!